Text: Panasonic Energy Corporation of America; Panasonic Energy Corporation of America is the premier manufacturer of powerful, energy efficient, long-lasting batteries. Located in the second largest city in Georgia, the historical city of Columbus, Panasonic Energy Corporation of America is the U.S. headquarters for Panasonic batteries.

Nestled in the heart of Muscogee county, the Panasonic hub of battery know-how consists of three state-of-the-art battery divisions. The Sales and Marketing division houses a packaging center, a warehouse and administrative offices which include Customer Service, Marketing, Packaging Development and Supply Chain. The Lithium battery division is the largest manufacturer of primary cylindrical lithium cells in North America. The Materials division manufactures battery components for customers worldwide.

Using stringent controls and advanced production techniques, Panasonic factories produce batteries to the highest quality and performance standards. Since 1931, Panasonic has been the trusted brand of choice for people around the globe. In the USA, our extensive product portfolio provides powerful solutions for a wide range of devices. Our feature brands are eneloop, eneloop pro, Platinum Power, Alkaline Plus Power, Lithium, and Super Heavy Duty Power.

Today’s market is fluid, ever-changing and always customer-focused. To address customers’ various requirements, we provide localization as well as market and customer-focused solutions. Our packaging flexibility and design expertise allow us to create tailor-made solutions expeditiously.

Excellence is at the heart of our business with quality, performance, safety and reliability as the key foundations. Other Sectors; Other Manufacturing;  Built Environment; Text: Patriot Renewable Energy Capital, LLC; Patriot Renewable Energy Capital, LLC (Patriot) is a tax equity solutions provider for renewable energy developers. Patriot invests in tax equity structures for solar, wind, hydro, battery and biomass projects. The Patriot team is comprised of skilled individuals with decades of experience and a proven track record in project development, finance, tax structuring and environmental management.

Patriot is actively seeking to partner with renewable asset developers, owners and operators to help monetize their investment tax credits (ITCs) and production tax credits (PTCs), enabling the development of clean renewable energy resources.

Our affiliate companies include Patriot Renewables, LLC, a developer, owner, and operator of utility-scale wind and solar energy projects, and Jay Cashman, Inc., a multifaceted contractor in marine construction, dredging, LNG tank construction, equipment leasing, real estate development and mechanical construction industries.
